<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 27 at 1:39PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...Elevated Fire Weather Conditions This Afternoon...
A combination of dry and breezy conditions will continue an
enhanced risk for the active spread of wildfires this afternoon.
West-northwest winds 10 to 20 mph, with gusts of 25 to 35 mph
will continue this afternoon. Humidity levels have fallen to 20
to 25 percent. This has resulted in elevated fire weather
conditions that would support rapid rates of spread for wildland
fires.
Residents are urged to exercise caution handling any potential
ignition source...including machinery... cigarettes...and matches.
Be sure to properly discard all smoking materials. Any dry
grasses and tree litter that ignite will have the potential to
spread quickly.</description>
